pageContext.claim: “When they went to Paul Ryan to get a subpoena because they found the same things that we are talking about, Paul would say, well, let's take it easy, let's not this, let’s come back in a week, let's see if we still think -- let's do this -- it was impossible. You couldn't get a subpoena. [Pelosi] hands out subpoenas like they are cookies.”
pageContext.analysis: This is nonsense. House Republicans (under then-Speaker Paul D. Ryan (R-Ohio) issued more than 70 subpoenas and letters between July 5 and Sept. 29, 2016 alone.
